(* This define is used to determine the compiler versions 
   as well compiler type being used to make compilation
   easier and more portable. The following defines will
   be created:
   
     TP = Turbo Pascal / Borland Pascal compiler versions
     Delphi1 = Delphi 2
     FPC1    = Freepascal
     
   Platform directives:
      LINUX
      WIN32
      WIN32
      MSWINDOWS
      MSDOS
      
   CPU Directives:
      CPU386
      CPU86
      
      
   Compiler information support:
   
   ASSEMBLER = Assembler syntax is supported (Defined in Delphi)
   UNICODE   = Unicode is the default string type (Defined in certain versions of Delphi)
   
   
   SUPPORTS_INT64          = Support for the int64 datatype.
   SUPPORTS_ASSERT        = Support for Assert system procedure
   SUPPORTS_WIDESTRING     = Support for the Widestring datatype.
   SUPPORTS_ANSISTRING     = Support for the AnsiString datatype
   SUPPORTS_LARGE_STREAMS  = Support for streams (64-bit)
   SUPPORTS_CLASSES        = Support for class type objects, otherwise only old format objects are supported.
   SUPPORTS_VARIANTS       = Support for Variant datatype
   SUPPORTS_POINTERMATH    = Possibility to do pointer arithmetic on typed 
             pointers such  ^Byte, and also permits to treat them as 0-based
             unbounded arrays, such as is supported for PChar datatype in older versions of
             Object pascal.
   SUPPORTS_INLINE         = Support for inline directive
   SUPPORTS_DYNARRAYS      = Support for dynamic arrays
   SUPPORTS_LONGWORD       = Support for longword data type
   DATASET_V1             = Supports Freepascal 1.0 / 2.0 / 2.2 datasets 
          (only the following field types are supported: ftString,ftSmallint,
                ftInteger,ftWord,ftBoolean,ftFloat,ftDate,ftTime,ftDateTime,ftBytes,
                ftVarBytes,ftAutoInc,ftBlob,ftMemo, ftGraphic,ftFmtMemo).
          Those versions of Freepascal, because of bugs, have serious issues with ftDateTime
          ftBlob, ftMemo, ftGraphic and ftFmtMemo and they should not be used.
   DATASET_V2             = Supports Freepascal 2.4+ and Delphi 4+ datasets.
   DATASET_V3             = Supports Freepascal 2.7+ and Delphi 2009+ datasets.
*)


